'''Connecticut's 4th Congressional District''' is currently represented in the [[111th United States Congress]] by [[Jim Himes]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]). Himes defeated Republican [[Chris Shays]] in November 2008, who had held the seat since 1987. From 2007 until 2009, the fourth district was the only district in [[New England]] to be represented by a Republican.

==Cities and towns==
The 4th district includes portions of [[Fairfield County, Connecticut|Fairfield]] and [[New Haven County, Connecticut|New Haven]] counties in [[southwestern Connecticut]]. The biggest cities in the district are Bridgeport and Stamford.

Cities and towns in the district include [[Bridgeport, Connecticut|Bridgeport]], [[Darien, Connecticut|Darien]], [[Easton, Connecticut|Easton]], [[Fairfield, Connecticut|Fairfield]], [[Greenwich, Connecticut|Greenwich]], [[Monroe, Connecticut|Monroe]], [[New Canaan, Connecticut|New Canaan]], [[Norwalk, Connecticut|Norwalk]], [[Oxford, Connecticut|Oxford]], [[Redding, Connecticut|Redding]], [[Ridgefield, Connecticut|Ridgefield]], [[Shelton, Connecticut|Shelton]] (part), [[Stamford, Connecticut|Stamford]], [[Trumbull, Connecticut|Trumbull]], [[Weston, Connecticut|Weston]], [[Westport, Connecticut|Westport]], and [[Wilton, Connecticut|Wilton]].

